                    p Taking this new branding, I created a wide range of digital and print assets, from business cards, pamphlets, letterheads, sponsorship packages, the countless social media graphics, and more. Furthermore, I also wrote copy for all social media graphics as well as the branding guidelines.
                    
                section
                    h3 Come full circle
                    div(class="img-wrapper")
                            img(src="img/SMA/smamily-gathering.jpg" data-src="img/SMA/smamily-gathering.jpg" data-action="zoom" alt="group photo with coordinators" class="blur lazyload")
                    p Just as I have received mentorship when I was a coordinator, another strong reason I wanted this role was to pass it forward and support others in their personal and professional development. It first begins with finding the right individual via interviews who would be good fit with SMA’s culture and would have a lot to gain from the mentorship. From then, I mentored coordinators one-on-one which involved creating project briefs and training documents, as well as providing constructive feedback and guidance on the work they produce. 
                    p For another department within SMA, I developed workshops that introduced design tools and skills to as many as 9-12 students at a time. Using Photoshop and Illustrator, I taught students how to create their own resumes and Facebook banners.
            
            div(class="container")
                h2 Reflection
                section
                    p One of the most important lessons I took away from is to be passionate in the work that you do. For MIF, our ticket sales were not performing very well at 3 weeks before the event day. The VP of Marketing came in and gave our organizing team an intense and passionate talk about how our drive to succeed was lackluster and wanted us to push harder so that when we look back on this in the future, we are proud that our efforts have led to a successful sold out event. And in no time at all, we sold of nearly 2 weeks before the event day and it was well received. That was a pivoting moment that shaped me to become more passionate which I have taken with me in the role as VP and beyond.
                    
